messages.text: Runaway with me?
Sure. Let me just pack my bags and we can go south of the border. LOL
I’m serious.
What your mom wouldn’t give you allowance again? You do know you need money to run away.
This isn’t about money. I just . . . I need to get out of here.
What happen babe? :(
They want to send me away.
Send you where?
Idk. Some place that’s going to cure the gay out of me.
I should have never told them.
I should have kept us a secret.
That’s no way to live your life.
You can’t just hide who you are from your family.
If they can’t accept you then that’s on them.
You don’t get it, Stan!
My parents aren’t like your. Being gay . . . being me is a sin.
That isn’t true.
It is true. It would have been better for everyone if I had never been born. My own mother can’t even look at me.
It’s not your fault if your family have problems. You’re an amazing person. Being gay doesn’t change all the good you do.
I just . . . I don’t know how much more of this I can take.
Don’t say things like that. I’m here for you. Lean on me.
Thanks, Stan.
I love you.
I love you too. I’m going to bed. Night.
Night babe. Sleep well.
Hey. Want to catch a movie with me. My treat.
Can’t. I’m in Church.
Lol. You’re not supposed to text in church.
It’s fine. God can’t see gay people.
Good. Means no one saw me just pick my nose.
Lol gross. Did you eat it?
Taste like bogger.
Are you feeling better than last night?
Idk. I asked my mom if we could talk. She said she would be willing to listen. I’m hoping at least maybe I won’t get sent away. Uk.
I don’t want you to go anywhere either. I’m right behind you babe. Support time hundred.
Thanks. I’ll text you after I get out of here.
Tell me how you talk goes.
Great news!
My mom said I can stay. She said she knows those places don’t help people. That it was my dad’s idea.
They’re going to talk. But she said she don’t want me that far away. So you know what that means.
A whole summer of lovin
Damn straight . . . Lol
I’m so happy. :D At least one of your parents aren’t idiots.
You want to come over?
Give me 30 mins.
Last night was amazing!!!!
I need to invite you over more often.
Hey how come you’re not in school today.
Carl answer me back already.
Carl I’m worried.
You missed school again today.
What’s going on?
Babe please text me back.
Day three Carl.
Where are you?
Should I call the cops?
Is everything okay?
I love you.
I saw you in the hall today.
What happened to your eye?
Hey, sorry I worried you.
I was grounded so my dad took my phone from me.
What happened to your eye?
It’s nothing. I walked into a wall.
Did that wall happen to be shaped like your father.
Don’t go silent on me. Answer me.
There nothing we can do okay. Just forget it.
Of course I won’t just forget it. You need to tell someone Carl. You need to get out of there.
And go where?
Who am I supposed to tell? What am I supposed to do?
You’re supposed to be healthy and safe. You can come here. I’ll ask my dad. He won’t care if you live with us.
I can’t do that. Plus it was just a one time deal.
My dad doesn’t normally drink that much so it will be okay.
I’m fine love.
Come over tonight at least. Let me kiss your boo boo.
Lol. I’ll see if I can sneak out.
I’m outside. Open your door.
I don’t think waking up next to you will ever get old.
You should have stayed longer it's the weekend.
I had to get home before my dad found out I was gone.
Oh yeah him.
I know a guy.
There never find the body.
Lol. This is why I love you.
And I thought it was because of my good looks.
Those help.
I got to go. I’ll text you later. Maybe I’ll come over tonight too.
I’ll be waiting.
What happened to you yesterday. You never texted.
Did you get grounded again?
Really you need to get better at this sneaking out part.
Or maybe we should buy burner phones so your dad can’t take our link away.
You’re MIA again.
I hate it when this happens. I get so anxious.
Carl please steal a phone and let me know you’re okay.
Did your dad do something?
It’s been a week Carl.
You have to come to school you know.
Is it me? Are you just avoiding me?
I love you. Please text me when you can.
I can’t do this anymore.
Where have you been?
Are you okay?
I can’t take this much longer.
I can’t be the son they want me to.
So don’t. You don’t have to be who they expect you to be. Just be yourself.
I’m trying so hard Stan. I just want my parents to love me for me.

It’s there lost if they can’t. I love you. I love the amazing person you are. I love how you give kids your lunch when they can’t get any. I love how you’re always willing to help a classmate in need. I love how you came up with the ideas to raise money for the art program. And how you’re never too busy to lend a shoulder to someone who going through something. I love how brave you are Carl. How even though you knew how your parents felt you still was strong enough to tell them about us. About you, the real you.
I feel so trap. Like . . . like there’s only one way out. And I know its the easy way out. But I want to take it, Stan.
That isn’t the answer. I’ll never forgive you if you take yourself from me. Just come over. Let’s talk.
I can’t stay here anymore. He’s going to kill me if I don’t get out.
Let's run away together.
You mean it?
I’m packing now. Meet me at the bus stop in 30 mins.
I love you.
I love you too.
I’m here. Where are you?
Carl tell me you made it out.
Please, please God don’t do this to me.
Carl, please. I’m here baby.
Oh god. Answer me. I’m here. I’m waiting.
Carl?
Carl?
I’m here. Look up. And stop crying.
